Cell.Data: Register Offset Aliasing and Access Testing
Checking the boundary conditions of the address of registers
Verifying the access(R/W) of CSR register, access (R/W) of DPR register, access (R/W) of CMDR register, access (RO) of FSMR register
Checking the default values of the valid registers by disabling the core using CSR register
Value written or read in one register should not affect the values in other registers
When the reset signal is detected, the value in CSR register should be '00000000'

Verifying the access(R/W) of Enable bit in CSR, access(R/W) of Interrupt Enable bit in CSR, access(RO) of Bus Busy bit in CSR, access(RO) of Bus Captured bit in CSR and access(RO) of Bus ID bit in CSR
When the reset signal is detected, the value in DPR register should be '00000000'
When the reset signal is detected, the value in CMDR register should be '10000000'

Verifying the access(R/W) of Done bit in CMDR, access(R/W) of Not Acknowledged bit in CMDR, access(RO) of Arbitration Lost bit in CMDR,access(RO) of Error indication bit in CMDR,access(RO) of Reserved bit in CMDR and access(R/W) of Command bit in CMDR
When the reset signal is detected, the value in FSMR register should be '00000000'
Verifying the access(RO) of Byte FSM bits in FSMR and access(RO) of Bit FSM bits in FSMR
Verify FSMR has correct values correspondin to CMDR commands.

Test cases to check that the bit level FSM is working correctly
All valid commands are recognized (State change)
All Invalid commands are ignored (State unchanged)
Valid commands make valid state transitions for Stable States
Test cases created to check bit level transitions from stable states are correct
Test cases created to check bit level transitions from idle state are correct
Start command in Idle state makes transition to StartA
When FSMR[3:0] = Idle, and Start Conition is detected- State should change to StartA
Stop, Write 0, Write 1, Read command in Idle state makes transition to Idle
When FSMR[3:0] = Idle, and Start Condition is not detected- State should not change
Test cases created to check bit level transitions from RWE state are correct
Start command in RWE State state makes transition to Rep-StartA
When FSMR[3:0] = RWE, and Start Condition is detected- State should change to Rep-StartA
Stop command in RWE State state makes transition to StopA
When FSMR[3:0] = RWE, and Stop Condition is detected- State should change to StopA
Write 0/ Write 1/ Read command in RWE state makes transition to RWA
When FSMR[3:0] = RWE, and Write 0/ Write 1/ Read Condition is detected- State should change to RWA
Test cases created to check bit level transitions from StartC state are correct
Start command in StartC state makes transition to StartC
When FSMR[3:0] = StartC, and Start Condition is detected- State should change to StartC
Write 0, Write 1, Read command in StartC state makes transition to RWA
When FSMR[3:0] = StartC, and Write 0/ Write 1/ Read Condition is detected- State should change to RWA
Stop command in StartC state makes transition to StopA
When FSMR[3:0] = StartC, and Stop Condition is detected- State should change to StopA

Test cases created to check bit level transitions from meta-stable states are correct
Start A to Start B after a delay HD_STA
if Bit Transition is at State "Start A" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay HD_STA it should transit to State : "Start B"
Start B to Start C after a delay HD_STA + VD_DAT
if Bit Transition is at State "Start B" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay HD_STA + VD_DAT it should transit to State : "Start C"
Stop A to Stop B after a delay TSU_DAT
if Bit Transition is at State "Stop A" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay TSU_DAT it should transit to State : "Stop B"
Stop B to Stop C after a delay TSU_STA
if Bit Transition is at State "Stop B" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay TSU_STA it should transit to State : "Stop C"
Stop C to IDLE on posedge of SCL
if Bit Transition is at State "Stop C" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay (SCL - TSU_STA) it should transit to State : "IDLE"
Repeated Start A transits to Repeated Start B after a delay TSU_STA
if Bit Transition is at State "Repeated Start A" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay TSU_STA it should transit to State : "Repeated Start B"
Repeated Start B transits to Repeated Start C after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "Repeated Start B" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay TSU_STA it should transit to State : "Repeated Start C"
Repeated Start C transits to Repeated Start A after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "Repeated Start C" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay it should transit to State : "Repeated Start A"
ReadWrite A transits to ReadWrite B after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "ReadWrite A" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay it should transit to State : "ReadWrite B"
ReadWrite B transits to ReadWrite C after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "ReadWrite B" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay it should transit to State : "ReadWrite C"
ReadWrite C transits to ReadWrite D after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "ReadWrite C" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay it should transit to State : "ReadWrite D"
ReadWrite C transits to IDLE after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "ReadWrite C" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay it should transit to State : "IDLE"
ReadWrite D transits to ReadWrite E after a delay
if Bit Transition is at State "ReadWrite D" in the FSMR Register, then after a fixed delay it should transit to State : "ReadWrite E"
